results.raw: Protesters Gathered After Man Shot, Killed by Police in Brooklyn Center at 6242 Lee Ave N, Minneapolis, MN, 55429, USA
results.rawLocation: 6242 Lee Ave N, Minneapolis, MN, 55429, USA
results.title: Protesters Gathered After Man Shot, Killed by Police in Brooklyn Center

-MY28bbkpwIwOtW3jo2W.text: Incident reported at 6242 Lee Ave N.

-MY28bh3HuwSjYBFS6lw.text: Citizen user video shows a group gathered in the area.

-MY2GReqCAq5iDyGdZnR.text: According to a tweet from the Minnesota Department of Public Safety Bureau of Criminal Apprehension, BCA agents and crime scene personnel are en route to an officer involved shooting incident in Brooklyn Center.

-MY39vAuvBF7t0VXiAUx.text: According to a local news source, Metro Transit is shutting down public transit in Brooklyn Center at the request of law enforcement.

-MY3cvor7ZATksRFwO-Z.text: According to a Tweet from the Minnesota State Patrol, Mobile Response Team units assisted with clearing the area near the Brooklyn Center strip mall. Units are also helping with traffic control.

nib.text:
A man was shot and killed by police during a traffic stop in Brooklyn Center on Sunday. Protesters and members of the man's family have gathered near the scene of the fatal altercation.

According to [CBS 4](https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2021/04/11/bca-reporting-to-officer-involved-shooting-in-brooklyn-center/), the 20-year-old man was pulled over for a traffic violation around 2 p.m.
During the stop,  police learned the man had an outstanding warrant and attempted to arrest him.

As the man began driving away, officers opened fire toward the car, which was occupied by the man and his girlfriend, striking him an unclear number of times.

The man then drove several blocks before crashing into another vehicle near 63rd Avenue North and Lee Avenue North.

The man was pronounced deceased at the scene.

Medics transported the man's girlfriend and an occupant in the other vehicle to an area hospital with minor injuries.

The BCA is involved in the ongoing investigation.

According to the [Star Tribune](https://www.startribune.com/relatives-police-in-plymouth-shot-man-20-who-then-drove-to-brooklyn-center-where-he-where-he-was-pro/600044821/?refresh=true), family members of the man killed have identified him as Duante Wright. They have gathered at the scene seeking answers.

Live video showed police officers lined up across the street as protesters continue gathering in the area.

Citizen will provide more details as they become available.
